==English==
===Etymology===
{{confix|en|xeno|phobic}}, from {{uder|en|grc|ξένος||foreign, strange}} + {{m|grc|φόβος||fear}}
===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}
# Exhibiting or characterised by [[xenophobia]], a fear or hatred of [[stranger]]s or [[foreigner]]s.
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=May 13, 2006|passage=Residents of Plettenberg Bay this week launched violent '''xenophobic''' attacks on foreign Africans living in informal settlements, beating them and ransacking their houses|work=Weekend Argus}}
#* {{quote-web|en|url=http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2019/may/17/the-guardian-view-on-the-venice-biennale-migrant-boat-pushing-the-limits-of-art|title=The Guardian view on the Venice Biennale’s migrant boat: pushing the limits of art|date=2019-05-17|work=The Guardian|passage=It has not yet promised much in the way of serious debate about the migrant crisis or the EU’s failure to tackle it in a humane and coordinated manner, in the context of the Italian government’s increasingly '''xenophobic''' policies.}}
